<A HREF="http://everquest.station.sony.com/downtime_fs.html" TARGET="_new"><B>Patch Day Reminder:</B></A><BR>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="arial">
Just a reminder that today is patch day (Tuesday, August 1st). All servers will be coming down at 7:00 am PDT for aproximately 6 hours.</FONT>
</FONT><BR><BR>

<A HREF="eqnews.php3"><B>Sony EQ Forum Changes Today:</B></A><BR>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="arial">
The official EverQuest forums at their <A HREF="http://everquest.station.sony.com/everquest_h.html" TARGET="_new">website</A> will be undergoing major changes today. New board rules will only allow current active subscribers of EverQuest to post on these forums, and a strict new code of conduct will start being enforced starting at the same time. Click this paragraphs title to go read what Abashi posted last night about this, as well as some comments I made on what I lthink of all this.</FONT><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="arial"><B>Editors Note:</B> Woops! Be helpful if I link to the right news article *grin*.</FONT><BR><BR>

<A HREF="maps.php3"><B>300 Maps!:</B></A><BR>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="arial">
With the addition of 6 maps by Torrid Brightflame of Druzzil Ro, the total number of maps now in our database is over 300! By far the most complete collection available anywhere. Many thanks to all the players who have taken up the trade of cartography!</FONT><BR><BR>

<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="verdana">1. <A HREF="map_search.php3?action=zone&add_zone=Burning%20Wood">Burning Wood</A> - By EQ Atlas</FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="verdana">2. <A HREF="map_search.php3?action=zone&add_zone=Emerald%20Jungle">Emerald Jungle</A> - By EQ Atlas</FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="verdana">3. <A HREF="map_search.php3?action=zone&add_zone=Chardok">Chardok</A> - 2 maps by Torrid Brightflame</FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="verdana">4. <A HREF="map_search.php3?action=zone&add_zone=Old%20Sebilis">Old Sebilis</A> - 2 maps by Torrid Brightflame</FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="verdana">5. <A HREF="map_search.php3?action=zone&add_zone=Trakanon's%20Teeth">Trakanon's Teeth</A> - By Torrid Brightflame</FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="verdana">6. <A HREF="map_search.php3?action=zone&add_zone=Plane%20of%20Fear">Plane of Fear</A> - By By Torrid Brightflame</FONT><BR><BR>


<A HREF="main.phtml#1.0 Poll"><B>Polls:</B></A><BR>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIEL">
Here are the results from the last poll. The question was <I>"Do you intend to purchase the expansion pack, The Scars of Velious, when it is released?"</I></FONT><BR><BR>

<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="arial, verdana">
1. Yes       76.08% (442 votes)<BR>
2. No        8.26% (48 votes)<BR>
3. Not Sure  15.66% (91 votes)<BR>
<B>-------------------</B><BR>
<B>Total Votes:</B> 581</FONT><BR><BR>

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIEL">
Well, it is pretty easy to see that most of our visitors will gladly purchase another expansion pack. Not suprising really, since anyone not interested in EQ anymore probably wouldn't be visiting sites like this still. But is still good to know that interest isn't dead in EQ yet. *grin*<BR><BR>

The poll this time is more serious. In light of the sweeping changes to the EQ forums over on the official site, I want to see what people's thoughts are. So the question this time will be... <I>"Which statement below best describes your thoughts on the Forum changes over at the Station?"</I>.</FONT><BR><BR>

<B><I>MadWand</I></B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>	
